# DURANDAL

*A personal media downloader. No sketchy sites. No bloat.*

---

**DURANDAL** is a desktop media downloader for Windows, built around the things that actually matter — YouTube, Spotify, X, and more — wrapped in a dark GUI inspired by the rogue AI from Bungie's *Marathon*. Fast, self-contained, and built for daily use.

[![Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/version-1.0.0-orange?style=flat-square)](https://github.com/Ceezay/Durandal/releases)
[![Platform](https://img.shields.io/badge/platform-Windows-blue?style=flat-square)]()
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-Personal-gray?style=flat-square)]()

</div>

---

## What it does

| Tab | What you get |
|-----|-------------|
| **YouTube** | MP4 or MP3, quality & FPS selection, playlists, clip trimming |
| **Spotify** | Tracks downloaded as MP3 via YouTube Music, with metadata & artwork embedded |
| **X (Twitter)** | Videos, native GIFs, and a video → GIF converter with speed & quality controls |
| **Art Grab** | Pull album and track artwork from YouTube or Spotify URLs |
| **GIF → MP4** | Convert any local GIF to MP4 with scale and FPS options |
| **Discord & Tenor** | Download attachments from Discord CDN links and Tenor GIFs |
| **Avatar Cropper** | Crop images or GIFs to standard avatar sizes with filters and quality presets |

---

## Getting started

1. Download the latest `.exe` from [Releases](https://github.com/Ceezay/Durandal/releases)
2. Run it — no installation required
3. On first launch it will set itself up automatically

That's it. No Python, no FFmpeg, no dependencies to install manually. Everything is handled on first run.

---

## Requirements

- Windows 10 or 11
- An internet connection on first launch

---

